cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper deals with computer vision techniques for analyzing histopathological breast cancer images. The paper proposes a complete pipeline for stain normalization, segmentation, and classification of nuclei in H&E stained images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses neural networks for segmentation and classification, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories. The use of an Information Maximizing Generative Adversarial Network (InfoGAN) for unsupervised classification makes cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible category. Finally, the paper also deals with image processing techniques, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible category.
